readPackets

public void readPackets(Connection connection)
                 throws IOException
Reads sequence of packets from the connection and sends them to registered output channels. This method does not exit until a possible control message is received (the first byte read following a packet is not an '$' character) or the calling thread is interrupted.

Parameters:
connection - - the connection from which to read interleaved packets.
Throws:
EOFException - - If the input stream reaches EOF or is closed.
IOException - - An I/O error occurred
